olive oil
2 radish
1 cucumber
1 punnet cherry tomatoes
1 packet tahini
1 packet Garlic Dip
1 packet flatbreads
1 packet pulled chicken
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 packet Mustard Cider Dressing
1 packet roasted almonds
1 bag herbs
1 sachet Middle Eastern spice blend
½ sachet Turkish Sumac Seasoning
1 packet Currants

• Trim and thinly slice radish. Thinly
slice cucumber. Halve tomatoes
• In a small bowl, combine tahini and
garlic dip
• Toast or grill flatbreads to your liking.

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
high heat. Cook chicken, seasonings and currants until browned and
fragrant, 3-4 mins
• In a large bowl, combine mixed leaves, radish, cucumber, tomatoes,
chicken mix and cider dressing.

• Roughly chop almonds
• Divide salad and flatbreads
between plates
• Top with almonds and torn herbs
• Serve drizzled with tahini and
garlic dressing